snippet vplug
alias vp vpl vim plug plu pl vi
  # `substitute(expand('%:p:h'), '.*\/', '', '')`

  `substitute(expand('%:p:h'), '.*\/', '', '')` is ${0:TARGET}

  ## Installation

  Install the plugin using your favorite package manager

  ### For dein.vim

  \`\`\`vim
  call dein#add('kaile256/`snip#vim#name_of_repo()`')
  \`\`\`

  If you set up dein to manage plugins in TOML,

  \`\`\`toml
  [[plugin]]
  repo = 'kaile256/`snip#vim#name_of_repo()`'
  \`\`\`

  This is recommended in lazy load:

  \`\`\`toml
  [[plugin]]
  repo = 'kaile256/`snip#vim#name_of_repo()`'
  on_${1:func} = ['${2:`snip#vim#prefix_for_function()`']
  hook_add = '''
  noremap <silent> ${3:#:key} :call `snip#vim#prefix_for_function()`${5:#:func_name}()<CR>
  '''
  \`\`\`

